# 2026-02-19 16:54:05.484886
+You are a senior Python engineer. Build a simple local web GUI for my UNSPSC hybrid retriever.
+
+Context:
+- I have a script `retrieve_bm25.py` that does hybrid retrieval: BM25 + Chroma vector + RRF fusion.
+- Inputs: a single text query (e.g., PO line item text / material short description).
+- Outputs: top N fused UNSPSC candidates with code + description + segment/family/class/commodity + debug ranks.
+
+Requirements:
+1) Use Python with a very simple web UI framework (prefer Streamlit first; if not, Gradio). No fancy frontend, just functional.
+2) The app should:
+   - Load indexes ONCE at startup:
+     - Chroma persistent collection: path `/projects/smc-cpg-classify/data/chroma_unspsc`, collection `unspsc_ref`
+     - BM25 pickle `/projects/smc-cpg-classify/data/index/bm25.pkl`
+     - BM25 ids `/projects/smc-cpg-classify/data/index/bm25_ids.pkl`
+     - Metadata parquet `/projects/smc-cpg-classify/data/index/bm25_meta.parquet`
+   - Load SentenceTransformer ONCE at startup.
+   - Provide:
+     - Text area for query
+     - Sliders/inputs for TOPK_BM25, TOPK_VEC, TOPK_FUSED, RRF_K
+     - Button “Search”
+   - Display results in a table with columns:
+     rank, code, description, segment, family, class, commodity, fused_score, bm25_rank, vec_rank
+   - Allow clicking a row to show the underlying `concat` path (from metadata) and/or the indexed document snippet.
+3) Performance:
+   - Cache heavy objects (model, chroma client, bm25) to avoid reloading per request.
+4) Safety:
+   - Force embeddings to CPU (device="cpu") and set env vars to disable ROCm/CUDA auto usage.
+5) Provide:
+   - `app.py` (the web GUI)
+   - minimal `requirements.txt` (or uv install commands)
+   - how to run: `streamlit run app.py`
+6) Keep code clean, with functions:
+   - normalize_query()
+   - retrieve_hybrid(query, topk_bm25, topk_vec, topk_fused, rrf_k)
+   - rrf_fuse()
+
+Deliver the full working code in one file (app.py) and instructions to run locally.
+

